# High Off My Love

"**High Off My Love**" is a track recorded by American media personality and recording artist [Paris Hilton](/Paris_Hilton), featuring the distinct vocal presence of rapper [Birdman](/Birdman_(rapper)). This particular [single](/Single_(music)) managed to see the light of day on May 5, 2015, though its journey to public consumption was, shall we say, protracted. The creative minds behind this piece include Hilton herself, alongside Charles D. Anderson, Corte "The Author" Ellis, Rondell "Mr. Beatz" Cobbs II, and [Bryan "Birdman" Williams](/Birdman_(rapper)). Production duties were handled with an almost clinical precision by Mr. Beatz.

Released on May&#160;5,&#160;2015&#160;(2015-05-05), "High Off My Love" traverses a few sonic landscapes, primarily settling within the realms of [dance-pop](/Dance-pop), [R&B](/Contemporary_R%26B), and [trap](/Trap_music). The explicit version clocks in at a somewhat generous 3 minutes and 45 seconds, while a cleaner, presumably less offensive, rendition runs for 3 minutes and 19 seconds. It was distributed under the watchful eyes of [Cash Money](/Cash_Money_Records) and [Universal](/Universal_Music_Group) record labels.

